or combinations for values 16-31.                 *Values 0,1,2,...,255 are permitted.                                             *                                                                                *  S = SHADOW command for changing shadow codes                                  *  C = More information on control operations                                    %S=SHADOW2? C=CONTRO?                                                            *@SELECT                                                                         *                                                                                *DIR?                                                                            @DIR <pathname>                                                                  *works like the OS command >DIR but gives the list of files                      *in the edit field below the current edit line.                                  *                                                                                *The DIR command is implemented as a part of a more general                      *desktop operation INDEX. Most of the specifications of INDEX                    *may be used to modify the output of DIR in various ways.                        *                                                                                *  I = Information on INDEX operation                                            *  C = More information on control operations                                    %C=CONTRO? I=INDEXKV?                                                            *                                                                                *LIFEGAME?                                                                       *LIFEGAME command starts "Game of Life" invented by by John Conway               *in 1970 and made popular by Martin Gardner in Scientific American.              *The game is played in Survo on a rectangular finite board of cells.             *By various specifications the original rules and the appearence of              *the game may be modified.                                                       *Original rules: At any time some of the cells will be alive or dead.            *The user determines the borders of the game board and living cells at           *the beginning as follows (use /BOX for drawing border lines):                   *                                                                                *LIFEGAME  / Activate this line!                                                 *         ษอออออออออออออออออออออออออออป                                          *         บ                           บ                                          *         บ           ***             บ                                          *         บ          ***              บ                                          *         บ           ***             บ                                          *         บ                           บ                                          *         บ                           บ                                          *         ศอออออออออออออออออออออออออออผ                                          *@C                                                                              *Game of Life in Survo (continued)                                               *                                                                                *Let's study a cell * surrounded by 8 others:                                    *                                                                                *                       123                                                      *                       8*4                                                      *                       765                                                      *                                                                                *If cell * is alive and it is surrounded by 4 or more living cells,              *it will die by `overcrowding'. Likewise if at most 1 of the neighbours          *are alive, the cell dies by `exposure'. In other cases the cell stays           *alive for the next generation.                                                  *If the cell is dead (empty), it will be born again if it has exactly            *3 living neighbours.                                                            *The cells on the borders are assumed to be dead all the time.                   *                                                                                *The rules for birth and death are given by ON and OFF specifications.           *Thus the original (default) setting is ON=3 OFF=0145678 .                       *@C                                                                              *Game of Life in Survo (continued)                                               *                                                                                *Other specifications:                                                           *NMAX       gives number of generations to be produced.                          *WAIT       gives time between successive gemerations to be displayed.           *LIFE       gives a list of characters to be used for marking living             *           cells. Also shadow characters may be employed for painting           *           successive generations with different colors.                        S           Example: LIFE=***                                                    *                                                                                *By studying the `screen saver' sucro /LIFEGAME still more specifications        *may be detected.                                                                *More information is found (in Finnish) by activating                            */ELOPELI                                                                        *@END                                